snippet: Turkey’s deployment of troops to the outskirts of Mosul in support of a training mission set off protests in Baghdad, where Iraqi authorities said they had not agreed to it.
abstract: Turkey withdraws troops outside Mosul, Iraq; deployment was meant to support training mission but it ended up angering Baghdad government, which says it did not agree to host Turkish forces.
lead_paragraph: Turkey’s deployment of troops to the outskirts of Mosul in support of a training mission set off protests in Baghdad, where Iraqi authorities said they had not agreed to it.

headline.main: After Protests, Turkey Withdraws Some Troops From Iraq
